      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS PEONY (6) has been within a length of the winner at her last three runs. Handy all the way but was just edged out of the placings in a busy finish last start over this distance at Dubbo. Has had plenty of chances but this looks a very winnable race from a favourable draw. REGALADE (3) had his first run since coming to the Brett Robb stable last time out and was easily accounted for over 1300m at Dubbo. Backs up just eight days later which is a positive sign. Can improve sharply against moderate opposition. NOTHING FINER (2) was ridden cold last start and closed with purpose to finish second over 1300m at Dubbo. Looms as a threat over an extra 100m today. FIERCE IMPULSE (5) is yet to fill a placing in eight starts and has been safely held in her three appearances this prep. Very fit and can sneak into the frame. ROCK'N ON UPTOWN (8) ran a much better race at Quirindi last time out and is in the mix if that wasn't a fluke.",
